<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-11-18T13:00:00-05:00" n="280" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d280">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">722.2315/2555: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-18T13:00:00-05:00">November 18, 1941—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:15 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>618. For the Under Secretary. Your telegram 461, November 17, 9 [<hi rend="italic">8</hi>] p.m. My Argentine and Brazilian colleagues
                                think the move is a desirable one but they wish to have the
                                Argentine and Brazilian Ambassadors at Washington clearly understand
                                that the Peruvian view is that the 1936 <hi rend="italic">status
                                    quo</hi> line can serve as a basis but with substantial
                                modifications in favor of Peru in the Oriente (Andoas and
                                Rocafuerte).</p>
                            <pb facs="0251" n="241" xml:id="pg_241"/>
                            <p>We are agreed that for political reasons no mention should be made of
                                President Prado, but his statements could be used as representing
                                the views of the Peruvian Government.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Norweb</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>